Posts.Content: waybacktexas wrote: I was going to make an appointment to get my limp checked out but then I realized, I will only be covered under my parents health insurance for another year. After that I will have to seek other coverage because I will be too old. If it does turn out to be cancer it would be considered a pre-existing condition. I could never afford the treatments on my own and I would not want my family to feel obligated to help me with the high costs. I think I will wait to see a dr and keep an eye on it for now.
